external_knowledge:
- 'John Doe' refers to a specific user in the system. ;
- The term 'project manager or owner' in this context can refer to either the internal project manager or the client project manager. ;
- The phrase 'distinct team names' means each team name is only listed once, even if it appears in multiple projects.

- 'pending invoices' refers to invoices that are still awaiting full payment; 
- 'partially or fully settled' means the payment status is 'paid', even if the invoice itself is not yet closed;
- 'the amount we're still waiting for' corresponds to the amount stated on the invoice.
